sources.title: UniFi Access Point/Switch/LTE | Releases | Ubiquiti Community

articles.author: UI-Glenn
articles.description:
Overview
This release has prioritized roaming performance for Gen2/Gen3/Gen6 APs, as well as improved topology reporting for Gen6 IW APs.
This release is available on the Official release channel for the models listed below. It's still a Release Candidate for all other models.

U6-Pro/Mesh/IW/Enterprise/Enterprise-IW

Improvements

Improved stability of wireless uplinks.
Automatically pick the best channel after an RF Scan if the AP Radio Channel is set to Auto.
Speed up the meshing reconnection after the uplink goes through a provision/reboot/firmware update.
[Gen2/Gen3/Gen6] Improved neighbor report accuracy.
[Gen2/Gen3/Gen6] Improve client connection and wireless uplink stability.
[Gen2/Gen3/Gen6] Improved neighbor report reliability to reflect neighboring AP channel changes.
